---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="About — Sage CG Venture Studio"
  description="Sage Consulting Group is a venture studio that starts, builds, and operates a small portfolio of software companies. Here's how the studio works and what we believe."
>
  <section class="border-b border-[var(--color-rule)]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pt-20 pb-12">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-[var(--color-muted)]">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-5xl sm:text-6xl tracking-tight">
        A studio, not a holding company.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-[var(--color-ink)]/75 leading-relaxed">
        Sage Consulting Group started as a consultancy. Over time it became a workshop — a place where the ideas we kept seeing in the field became their own companies. Today, Sage CG is the venture studio that owns and operates that portfolio.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose-about">
    <h2>What a venture studio is</h2>
    <p>
      An accelerator picks winners. A holding company buys them. A venture studio <em>builds</em> them — from the inside, using a shared team, shared infrastructure, and a long-term operator mindset.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each company in our portfolio is one we started ourselves or grew out of work we were already doing. They keep independent brands, products, and economics. The studio is the spine; the companies are the body.
    </p>

    <h2>How we decide what to build</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Real pain.</strong> If we can't point to a specific person who's miserable about a specific problem, we don't ship.</li>
      <li><strong>Fair market.</strong> Big enough to matter, small enough to be ignored by giants.</li>
      <li><strong>Operator advantage.</strong> Something about the team, the network, or the stack gives us a real edge.</li>
      <li><strong>Path to durability.</strong> A plausible road to a profitable, lasting business — not just a fundable one.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>What we share across companies</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Design system, brand toolkit, and component library</li>
      <li>Engineering platform, CI/CD, observability</li>
      <li>Back office: legal, finance, HR, vendor relationships</li>
      <li>Hard-won playbooks for launch, growth, and support</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Take outside capital for the studio itself</li>
      <li>Chase trends we can't operate inside of</li>
      <li>Pretend to be bigger than we are</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>
    <p>
      Working on something adjacent? Looking to collaborate, partner, or join one of the portfolio teams? <a href="/contact">Say hello</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  .prose-about { color: var(--color-ink); font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .prose-about h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 2rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .prose-about p { margin: 1rem 0; }
  .prose-about ul, .prose-about ol { margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .prose-about ul { list-style: disc; }
  .prose-about ol { list-style: decimal; }
  .prose-about li { margin: 0.35rem 0; }
  .prose-about a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; text-decoration-color: var(--color-rule); }
  .prose-about a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent); }
  .prose-about strong { font-weight: 600; }
  .prose-about em { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-style: italic; }
</style>
